    • Method Detail

      • validateArgument

        boolean validateArgument(User sender,
                         String[] label,
                         T arg)
        Validates that the argument is in the correct state. This should also send any and all error messages associated with the problem with the argument.
        Parameters:
        sender - the sender of the command.
        label - the label of the command
        arg - the argument to be validated.
        Returns:
        true if the argument is valid. false of the argument is not valid.
